<DocsLayout title="Spec Format v0.2" description="Reference for the pecto behavior specification format.">

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>pecto outputs structured behavior specs in YAML or JSON. The format is language-agnostic — the same structure represents Java and C# projects.</p>

<h2>Top-level structure</h2>
<pre><code>name: my-app
analyzed: '2026-03-25T14:30:00Z'
files_analyzed: 86
capabilities: [...]
dependencies: [...]
domains: [...]</code></pre>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>name</code></td><td>string</td><td>Project name (from directory name)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>analyzed</code></td><td>string</td><td>ISO 8601 UTC timestamp</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>files_analyzed</code></td><td>number</td><td>Total source files processed</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>capabilities</code></td><td>array</td><td>Extracted behaviors grouped by source</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>dependencies</code></td><td>array</td><td>Edges between capabilities</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>domains</code></td><td>array</td><td>Business domain clusters</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Capability</h2>
<p>A capability groups related behaviors from a single source file.</p>
<pre><code>- name: user-controller
  source: src/UserController.java
  endpoints: [...]
  operations: [...]
  entities: [...]
  scheduled_tasks: [...]</code></pre>

<p>Empty arrays are omitted from output.</p>

<h2>Endpoint</h2>
<pre><code>- method: POST
  path: /api/users
  input:
    body:
      name: CreateUserRequest
      fields:
        email: String
        name: String
    path_params:
      - name: id
        type: Long
        required: true
    query_params:
      - name: status
        type: String
  validation:
    - field: email
      constraints: ["@NotBlank", "@Email"]
  behaviors:
    - name: success
      returns:
        status: 201
        body:
          name: User
    - name: not-found
      returns:
        status: 404
  security:
    authentication: required
    roles: ["hasRole('ADMIN')"]
    cors: "origins: https://example.com"
    rate_limit: "rate-limiter: apiLimit"</code></pre>

<h2>Behavior</h2>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>name</code></td><td>string</td><td><code>success</code>, <code>not-found</code>, <code>conflict</code>, etc.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>condition</code></td><td>string?</td><td>When this behavior occurs</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>returns.status</code></td><td>number</td><td>HTTP status code</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>returns.body</code></td><td>TypeRef?</td><td>Response type with fields</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>side_effects</code></td><td>array</td><td>What the code does beyond returning</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Side Effects</h2>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Kind</th><th>Fields</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>db_insert</code></td><td><code>table</code></td><td>Insert via orderRepository</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>db_update</code></td><td><code>description</code></td><td>Delete via EF Core</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>event</code></td><td><code>name</code></td><td>OrderCreatedEvent</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>call</code></td><td><code>target</code></td><td>paymentService.charge</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Entity</h2>
<pre><code>- name: Owner
  table: owners
  fields:
    - name: id
      type: Integer
      constraints: ["@Id", "@GeneratedValue"]
    - name: firstName
      type: String
      constraints: ["@NotBlank"]</code></pre>

<h2>Operation</h2>
<pre><code>- name: createOrder
  source_method: OrderService#createOrder
  input:
    name: CreateOrderRequest
  transaction: required
  behaviors:
    - name: success
      returns:
        status: 200
      side_effects:
        - kind: db_insert
          table: orderRepository
        - kind: event
          name: OrderCreatedEvent</code></pre>

<h2>Scheduled Task</h2>
<pre><code>- name: hourlyCleanup
  schedule: "cron: 0 0 * * * *"

- name: handleOrderCreated
  schedule: "event: OrderCreatedEvent"
  description: Handles OrderCreatedEvent events</code></pre>

<h2>DependencyEdge</h2>
<pre><code>dependencies:
  - from: user-controller
    to: user-service
    kind: calls
    references:
      - "UserController#getById → userService.findById"</code></pre>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Kind</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>calls</code></td><td>Service-to-service or controller-to-service</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>queries</code></td><td>Service-to-repository or DbContext</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>listens</code></td><td>Event listener to event publisher</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>validates</code></td><td>Controller to DTO type</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Domain</h2>
<pre><code>domains:
  - name: user
    capabilities:
      - user-controller
      - user-entity
      - user-service
    external_dependencies:
      - order</code></pre>

<h2>Versioning</h2>
<p>Current version: <strong>v0.2</strong> (stabilizing). Breaking changes will increment the major version.</p>

</DocsLayout>
